const _familiar_vampire_squid = {title: "Vampire Squid (Familiar)", jsx: <><p><em>This eerie-looking squid has red eyes and webbing between its hook-lined tentacles.</em></p>
<p className="statblockHeaderFull"><span>Vampire Squid</span><span>CR 1/2</span></p>
<p><strong>Sources</strong> <Link to="/source/ultimate_wilderness">Ultimate Wilderness pg. 208</Link><br/><strong>XP</strong> 200<br/>N Tiny <Link to="/type/animal">animal</Link><br/><strong>Init</strong> +2; <strong>Senses</strong> darkvision 60 ft., low-light vision; Perception +1</p><p className="statblockSubHeader">Defense</p>
<p><strong>AC</strong> 14, touch 14, flat-footed 12 (+2 Dex, +2 size)<br/><strong>hp</strong> 5 (1d8+1)<br/><strong>Fort</strong> +3, <strong>Reflex</strong> +6, <strong>Will</strong> +1<br/><strong>Defensive Abilities</strong> pressure adaptation</p><p className="statblockSubHeader">Offense</p>
<p><strong>Speed</strong> swim 20 ft.<br/><strong>Melee</strong> bite +0 (1d3-2), tentacles +0 (<Link to="/umr/grab">grab</Link>)<br/><strong>Space</strong> 2-1/2, <strong>Reach</strong> 0<br/><strong>Special Attacks</strong> photophores</p><p className="statblockSubHeader">Statistics</p>
<p><strong>Str</strong> 6, <strong>Dex</strong> 15, <strong>Con</strong> 12, <strong>Int</strong> 2, <strong>Wis</strong> 13, <strong>Cha</strong> 3<br/><strong>Base Atk</strong> +0; <strong>CMB</strong> +0; <strong>CMD</strong> 8<br/><strong>Feats</strong> <Link to="/feat/lightning_reflexes">Lightning Reflexes</Link><br/><strong>Skills</strong> Stealth +14, Swim +10</p><p className="statblockSubHeader">Ecology</p>
<p><strong>Environment</strong> any oceans<br/><strong>Organization</strong> solitary, pair, or school (3-8)</p><p className="statblockSubHeader">Special Abilities</p>
<p><strong>Photophores (Ex)</strong> Once per day as a standard action while underwater, the vampire squid can release a 15-foot cone of disorienting bioluminescent mucus from its photophores, illuminating the area with <Link to="/rule/dim_light">dim light</Link>. A creature within this shimmering cloud of blue light must succeed at a DC 11 Fortitude save or be <Link to="/misc/dazzled">dazzled</Link> for as long as it remains in the cloud and for 1 round thereafter. The cloud persists for 1d4+1 rounds. The save DC is Constitution-based.</p>
<p><strong>Pressure Adaptation (Ex)</strong> A vampire squid takes no <Link to="/rule/pressure_damage">pressure damage</Link> from changes in water depth.</p>
<p><strong>Tentacles (Ex)</strong> A vampire squid's tentacles all strike as a single primary attack but only to <Link to="/rule/grapple">grapple</Link>.</p>
<p className="statblockSubHeader">Description</p>
<p>The vampire squid - so called for its red eyes and cloak-like webbing - is a cephalopod from the lightless depths of the oceans. This eerie mollusk is covered in photophores, which it can use to create a defensive barrage of light when agitated.</p>
<p>A vampire squid can reach a total body length of up to 1 foot and weighs 1 pound.</p>
<p><strong>Family:</strong> <Link to="/family/familiar">Familiar</Link></p>
</>};
